article.headline: Texas Southern 72, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 64
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Sollie Norwood scored 17 points for Texas Southern, which beat Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 72-64 Friday night in the Islanders' first game since a surprise showing in the NCAA tournament. David Burrell added 13 points off the bench in beating Texas A&M-Corpus Christi, who nearly upset second-seeded Wisconsin in their first NCAA tournament appearance last spring. Chris Daniels, the reigning Southland Conference Player of the Year, led the Islanders with 19 points. Kevin Perkins scored 16 and Justin Reynolds added 14. Jacques Jones blocked five shots and scored 12 points for Texas Southern (1-0). Daniels, who briefly made himself eligible for the NBA draft last spring before withdrawing his name, hit 7 of 13 shots from the field, including four 3-pointers for the Islanders (0-1).
